HOUSE BILL NO. HB0114
Protecting religious assembly in states of emergency act.
Sponsored by: Representative(s) Smith, S and Senator(s)
Hutchings
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to public health and safety; requiring
2 rules enacted during public health emergencies to provide
3 exemptions for religious assembly as specified; providing
4 for enforcement and remedies; authorizing a cause of
5 action; providing exceptions to the Wyoming Governmental
6 Claims Act; making conforming amendments; and providing for
7 an effective date.
8
9 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
10
11 Section 1. W.S. 35-4-116 is created to read:
12
13 35-4-116. Public health emergencies; religious
14 assembly exemptions.
15
1 HB0114

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0393
1 (a) For any order, rule, regulation, policy or
2 directive issued during a public health emergency as
3 defined by W.S. 35-4-115(a)(i) that requires the closure of
4 or otherwise limits a business or other entity from
5 remaining open and that exempts, in whole or in part, any
6 business or entity from those closure requirements or
7 limitations, the order, rule, regulation, policy or
8 directive shall provide the same exemption to:
9
10 (i) Any place of worship qualifying as an exempt
11 organization for religious purposes under section 501(c)(3)
12 of the federal Internal Revenue Code;
13
14 (ii) Churches, their integrated auxiliaries and
15 conventions or associations of churches;
16
17 (iii) Any gathering for religious assembly in
18 any place otherwise open for religious assembly, including
19 those taking place in private residences and public places.
20
21 (b) This section shall be construed to afford to
22 religious institutions, places of worship and religious
23 assemblies the same degree of freedom to meet during public
2 HB0114

