1 health emergencies as is afforded to any business or entity
2 that is exempted from closure requirements implemented
3 during a public health emergency.
4
5 (c) Any person aggrieved by a violation of this
6 section may bring a civil action for relief in any court of
7 competent jurisdiction. A court may, for an act or practice
8 that violates this section:
9
10 (i) Award damages, costs and attorney fees;
11
12 (ii) Issue a declaratory judgment for or enjoin
13 an act or practice that violates this section;
14
15 (iii) Award exemplary or punitive damages, if
16 the act or practice that violates this section was wanton
17 or malicious.
18
